<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;While Asian Americans have been central to the debate over affirmative action in education, we have also been all but silenced in it. Here, finally, Poonâ€”one of our leading scholarsâ€”restores the record. With courage and rigor but most of all bottomless empathy and heart, she debunks the false narratives and reveals the complexities of how Asian Americans actually feel about race and the future. An intimate, indispensable portrait of Asian America.&#8221;<br />
